cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PL

This paper discusses the virtualization of network resources and the challenges of mapping performance specifications to resource allocation. This topic is closely related to computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes a method for predicting service performance based on a VNF profile, which involves system modeling and control (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of network functions using software (cs.PL).
